UserComments.Comment: These spaces are right by the entrance, so are nearly constantly ICEd. There are signs but there is absolutely no enforcement. A complete waste of time - don't bother trying to use them.

Despite Tesco assuring me months ago that these would be made EV only parking spots, they are still regularly occupied by non-EV cars as the spaces are highly sought after, right next to the store entrance.

MediaItems.Comment: Picture shows the charging units mounted on the wall. It also shows some demo vehicles from a local garage blocking access to the spaces with the approval of Tesco!

AddressInfo.Title: Tesco Extra - Stourbridge
AddressInfo.AccessComments: 4 charge points immediately right at the bottom of the car park entry ramp and 4 more on the floor below in the corresponding place.

GeneralComments:
These spaces have now all been set with their active supply on, so no need to contact Customer Services to unlock them. There is also signage indicating that the spaces are for EV's only but these are frequently ignored by ICE's in all but the quietest periods of the day as they are so close to the entrance.
